  <li><a href={`${base}stanton/arccorp/`}>ArcCorp — The Factory World</a></li>
  <li><a href={`${base}stanton/microtech/`}>microTech — The Frozen Colony</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>System Overview</h2>
<p>The Stanton system is where the UEE tests corporate sovereignty. Four megacorporations, four planets, and not a single government strong enough to say no. The result is a patchwork of industrial ambition, environmental catastrophe, and financial excess that serves as both pride and warning of what happens when capital owns the sky.</p>

<h3>Planets</h3>
<dl>
  <dt><strong>Hurston (Stanton I)</strong></dt>
  <dd>A super-earth owned by Hurston Dynamics. Once a savannah. Now a strip mine with a city on it. The sunsets are orange from particulate matter and genuinely beautiful, which is the most Hurston thing about it.</dd>

  <dt><strong>Crusader (Stanton II)</strong></dt>
  <dd>A low-mass gas giant with a breathable upper atmosphere. Crusader Industries built a city in the clouds, because the alternative was admitting physics had won. The shipyards are the largest in the system.</dd>

  <dt><strong>ArcCorp (Stanton III)</strong></dt>
  <dd>A super-earth covered in factories, habitation blocks, and the kind of neon that makes you think someone designed the whole planet to be seen from orbit. Technically habitable. Technically.</dd>

  <dt><strong>microTech (Stanton IV)</strong></dt>
  <dd>A terraform-error cold world owned by microTech. The lakes are frozen, the clouds are permanent, and the corporate architecture is at its most absurdly pristine. The contrast between the polished city and the hostile terrain is sharp enough to cut.</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Asteroid Belts</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Aaron Halo</strong> — Between Crusader and ArcCorp. A major harvesting and mining zone. Dangerous, profitable, and exactly the kind of place a guide should warn you about.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Travel Notes</h3>
<p><strong>Visa:</strong> Not required for UEE citizens. Corporate security has jurisdiction on-world; expect different rules on each planet.</p>
<p><strong>Currency:</strong> UEC everywhere. Corporate scrip accepted on some worlds at slightly worse exchange rates.</p>
<p><strong>Language:</strong> Standard Galactic English. Local dialects exist on each corporate world.</p>
<p><strong>Health:</strong> Bring a filter mask for Hurston. Insulated gear for microTech. A lawyer for ArcCorp.</p>

<h3>Getting There</h3>
<p>Stanton is one of the most accessible systems in the UEE. Major jump points connect to Terra, Pyro, and Magnus. Once inside, quantum travel links the four planets. Surface travel varies by world — ground vehicles recommended for Hurston and microTech, VTOL-capable craft for Crusader.</p>

